QUESTION: What is maternity leave?
================================================================================

[Qwen2.5-7B] (sem_sim=0.760, lat=10.34s)
Maternity leave entitles female workers who have served at least six months during the past year to receive unpaid leave extending up to eight weeks based on certain conditions:

- Two weeks before the expected date of delivery plus four weeks post-delivery or following an abortion, both fully compensated according to usual earnings ("Art. 131").

- Extensions due to health issues related to pregnancy, childbirth, etc., might occur depending on available leave credits ("Art. 131(b)").

- Only the first four deliveries qualify for payment per woman since the implementation of PD 442 ("Art. 131(c)").

[LLaMA-3.1-8B] (sem_sim=0.716, lat=5.45s)
Maternity leave refers to time off granted to female workers before and after childbirth, typically lasting around eight weeks based on Art. 131(b): "The maternity leave shall be extended without pay on account of illness medically certified to arise out of the pregnancy..."

[Gemma-2-9B] (sem_sim=0.796, lat=9.78s)
Maternity leave provides eligible female employees time off before and after childbirth.   Under Article 131, every employer must grant a minimum of six weeks of paid maternity leave followed by up to four additional unpaid weeks depending on circumstances like complications during birth. This code outlines requirements for eligibility, duration, and payment structure.

